name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen submission
On May 26, the TV series "Kuang Biao" which was previously popular in China was criticized by netizens, who accused it of promoting the underworld, whitewashing the underworld, and deliberately suppressing the image of the people's police.
The cause of the incident was that in the recently announced list of nominees for the Shanghai TV Festival Magnolia Award, "Kuang Biao" was nominated for many awards, but the popular villain No. 1 Zhang Songwen was not nominated. Instead, the decent No. 1 Zhang Yi, who was previously criticized by netizens for his mediocre performance, was nominated for the best actor, causing netizens to speak up for Zhang Songwen.
The incident quickly escalated from an acting issue to an ideological dispute, and some netizens even raised the banner of "the big villain should not be nominated."
